os.es/noticia/2707004/0/disney-channel-estreno/soy-luna-violetta/|title=Disney Channel prepara el estreno de 'Soy Luna', la heredera del super\u00e9xito 'Violetta'|work=20minutos Espa\u00f1a|last=\u00c1lvarez|first=Isra|date=March 31, 2016|accessdate=June 22, 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n| company                  = [[Pol-ka]]<ref name=\"am\">{{cite web |url=http://www.produ.com/television/noticia.html?IDNoti=132934|title=Disney Latinoam\u00e9rica present\u00f3 las producciones originales para sus tres canalesBRUNO14MPD1, 2015|work=Produ Corporativo|accessdate=November 21, 2015|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n| distributor              = Disney Channel Latin America and [[Europe, the Middle East and Africa|EMEA]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])<ref name=\"a4\" />\n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2016|3|14}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|2018|8|17}}\n| related                  = <!-- To be used only for remakes, spin-offs, and adaptations. -->\n| website                  = http://disneychannel.disneylatino.com/soy-luna\n| image_size               = \n| image_alt                = \n| screenplay               = {{plainlist|\n* Gabriela Fiore\n* Jorge Edelstein\n}}\n| story                    = \n| budget                   = \n| channel                  = [[Disney Channel Latin America]]\n}}\n\n'''''Soy Luna''''' ([[English language|English]]: ''I am Luna'') is an Argentine [[telenovela]] produced by [[Disney Channel Latin America]]. The first episode of Soy Luna premiered with over 2.3 million views in Argentina alone. Developed by [[Disney Channel Latin America]] and produced by [[Disney Channel (Europe, Middle East, and Africa)|Disney Channel Europe, the Middle East and Africa]] (EMEA), the series stars [[Karol Sevilla]] along with [[Ruggero Pasquarelli]].<ref name=\"a4\"> {{cite web |url=http://peru.com/entretenimiento/telenovelas/disney-channel-estrenara-telenovela-juvenil-soy-luna-noticia-368517 |title=Disney Channel estrenar\u00e1 telenovela juvenil 'Soy Luna' |author=|date= |website= |work=Per\u00fa.com|accessdate=June 21, 2015|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=\"at\">{{cite web |url=http://www.elmundo.es/happy-fm/2015/06/16/55804d5cca47411a4d8b45ae.html |title=Conoce a los Personajes de 'Soy Luna', la Serie Sustituta de Violetta |author=|date= |website= |work=El Mundo Espa\u00f1a|accessdate=June 21, 2015|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://teleprograma.fotogramas.es/telenovela/2015/junio/soy-luna-telenovela-juvenil-disney-channel|title='Soy Luna', otra apuesta de Disney Channel|author=L.Cibeau|date= |website= |work=Teleprograma.fotogramas.es|accessdate=July 30, 2015|language=Spanish}}</ref> It premiered on March 14, 2016, and concluded on 17 August 2018.<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WnJxut5C6yY|title=Soy Luna: Nuevo tr\u00e1iler|time=0:56|website=YouTube|author=DisneyChannelLA|date=February 7, 2016|accessdate=February 15, 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Disney: telenovela teen Soy Luna se estrena el 14 de marzo|url=http://diariocorreo.pe/espectaculos/disney-telenovela-teen-soy-luna-se-estrena-el-14-de-marzo-655031/|website=diariocorreo.pe|accessdate=February 21, 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n== Series overview ==\n{{Main article|List of Soy Luna episodes|label 1=List of ''Soy Luna'' episodes}}\n{{:List of Soy Luna episodes}}\n\n=== Season 1 (2016) ===\n{{see also|Soy Luna (season 1)}}\nLuna Valente lives with her family in [[Canc\u00fan]], [[Mexico]]. She goes to school, has her own group of friends, has a job, and loves to skate. However, her life changes when her parents are given a job offer that moves them to [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]]. There she finds a skating rink named ''Jam & Roller'' where she learns free styling. She makes new friends and falls in love with Matteo Balsano.<ref name=\"am\" /> Also she sees interesting dreams about her childhood. She wants to learn her past.\n\n=== Season 2 (2017) ===\n{{see also|Soy Luna (season 2)}}\nThe holidays are over and everyone returns home. Luna walks to a revealing truth, with illusion, in her reunion with Matteo. No one knows the secret that Matteo hides, but Luna is willing to fight with the wind and the air to find out. Over time, Luna helps Matteo to discover his true passion and he must cope with the pressure of his demanding father. In the Benson mansion is a tense atmosphere after the arrival of Alfredo, father of Mrs. Sharon, changes the routine and brings back memories of the past. Luna feels a strong sympathy for this funny man who looks so much alike. Their relationship, with the help of Nina, marks a new personal path for Luna and helps investigate the mysteries of her past. Holiday conflicts affect the group of others. Amber, Jasmine, Delfi, Gast\u00f3n, Ramiro and Matteo who are finishing their studies, must decide which way to go.\n\n=== Season 3 (2018) ===\nLuna/Sol, has returned with her adoptive parents and her grandfather to the Benson mansion in Argentina. The mansion is now theirs. Amber has changed her clothing style to gothic. A new boy named Erik has fallen in love with Nina and becomes a couple. Sharon wants to take revenge on her father and the Valentes and decides to go back to Buenos Aires in disguise.\nLater in the season, Amber regained her normal clothing style and became a couple with Simon. During the big season finals, the Roller team started performing with the song \"Todo Puede Cambiar\" and Luna and Matteo are back together again. Amber, Delfi and Jazmin have made up for it and are friends again. At the end Luna celebrates her 18th birthday, concluding the series.\n\n== Cast and characters ==\n{{Main article|List of Soy Luna characters|l1=List of ''Soy Luna'' characters}}\n{{Div col|colwidth=25em}}\n====Introduced in season one====\n* [[Karol Sevilla]] as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Luna Valente|Luna Valente]]\n* [[Ruggero Pasquarelli]] as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Matteo Balsano|Matteo Balsano]]\n* [[Valentina Zenere]] as [[List of Soy Luna characters#\u00c1mbar Smith|\u00c1mbar Smith]]\n* [[Michael Ronda]] as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Sim\u00f3n \u00c1lvarez|Sim\u00f3n \u00c1lvarez]]\n* Malena Ratner as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Delfina Alzamendi|Delfina \"Delfi\" Alzamendi]]\n* Agust\u00edn Bernasconi as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Gast\u00f3n Perida|Gast\u00f3n Perida]] (seasons 1\u20132; guest season 3)\n* Katja Mart\u00ednez as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Jazm\u00edn Carbajal|Jazm\u00edn Carbajal]]\n* Ana Jara as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Jimena Medina|Jimena \"Jim\" Medina]]\n* Jorge L\u00f3pez as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Ramiro Ponce|Ramiro Ponce]]\n* Chiara Parravicini as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Yamila S\u00e1nchez|Yamila \"Yam\" S\u00e1nchez]]\n* Gast\u00f3n Vietto as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Pedro Arias|Pedro Arias]]\n* Lionel Ferro as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Nicol\u00e1s Navarro|Nicol\u00e1s \"Nico\" Navarro]]\n* [[Carolina Kopelioff]] as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Nina Simonetti|Nina Simonetti]]\n* Luz Cipriota as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Tamara R\u00edos|Tamara R\u00edos]] (season 1; guest season 2)\n* Lucila Gandolfo as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Sharon Benson|Sharon Benson]]\n* Rodrigo Pedreira as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Reinaldo Guitierrez|Reinaldo \"Rey\" Guitierrez]]\n* David Mur\u00ed as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Miguel Valente|Miguel Valente]]\n* Ana Carolina Valsagna as [[List of Soy Luna characters#M\u00f3nica Valente|M\u00f3nica Valente]]\n* Diego Sassi as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Tino|Tino]] (seasons 1\u20132)\n* Germ\u00e1n Tripel as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Cato|Cato]] (seasons 1\u20132)\n* Antonella Querzoli as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Amanda|Amanda]] (seasons 1\u20132)\n* Paula Kohan as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Mora Barza|Mora Barza]] (seasons 1\u20132; guest season 3)\n* [[Ezequiel Rodr\u00edguez (actor)|Ezequiel Rodr\u00edguez]] as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Ricardo Simonetti|Ricardo Simonetti]] (seasons 1\u20132; guest season 3)\n* Caro Ibarra as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Ana Castro|Ana Castro]]\n\n====Introduced in season two====\n* Estela Ribeiro as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Juliana|Juliana]] (seasons 2\u20133)\n* [[Roberto Carnaghi]] as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Alfredo Benson|Alfredo Benson]] (seasons 2\u20133)\n* Giovanna Reynaud as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Emilia|Emilia]] (season 3; recurring season 2)\n* Pasquale Di Nuzzo as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Benicio|Benicio]] (season 3; recurring season 2)\n* Joaqu\u00edn Berthold as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Gary L\u00f3pez|Gary L\u00f3pez]] (season 3; recurring season 2)\n\n====Introduced in season three====\n* Jandino as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Eric|Eric]] \n* Vicky Su\u00e1rez Battan as [[List of Soy Luna characters#Maggie|Maggie]] \n* [[Mia Jenkins]] as Emma \n*Esteban Vel\u00e1squez  as Michel\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Music==\n\n===Soundtrack albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:19.5em;\" | Soundtrack details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"8\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14em;\"| [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Argentine Chamber of Phonograms and Videograms Producers|ARG]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.capif.org.ar/rankings.aspx|title=\nRankings|work=[[Argentine Chamber of Phonograms and Videograms Producers]]|accessdate=June 22, 2016}} \n*For ''Soy Luna'': select \"Ventas F\u00edsicas Mensual\", \"2016\" and \"Febrero\".\n*For ''M\u00fasica en T\u00ed'': select \"Ventas F\u00edsicas Mensual\", \"2016\" and \"Agosto\".\n*For ''La vida es un sue\u00f1o'': select \"Ventas F\u00edsicas Mensual\", \"2017\" an