{"title_page": "Dilip Ghosh (politician)", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian Member of Parliament}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name          = Dilip Ghosh\n| image         = Dilip Ghosh MP.jpg\n| image_size    = 200px\n| caption       = \n| office1       = [[Member of Parliament (India)|Member of Parliament]], [[Lok Sabha]]\n| constituency1 = [[Medinipur (Lok Sabha constituency)|Medinipur]]\n| term_start1   = 23 May 2019\n| term_end1     = \n| predecessor1  = [[Sandhya Roy]]\n| successor1    = \n| office3       = [[Bharatiya Janata Party, West Bengal|9th President of Bharatiya Janata Party - West Bengal]] \n| assembly      = [[Member of Legislative Assembly|Member of West Bengal Legislative Assembly]]\n| term_start3   = 2015\n| term_end3     = \n| predecessor3  = Rahul Sinha\n| office2       = [[Member of Legislative Assembly|Member of West Bengal Legislative Assembly]]\n| constituency2 = [[Kharagpur Sadar (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Kharagpur Sadar]]\n| term_start2   = 2016\n| term_end2     = 23 May 2019\n| predecessor2  = [[Gyan Singh Sohanpal]]\n| successor2    = [[Pradip Sarkar]]\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age | 1 August 1964 |df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Jhargram district|Kuliana]], [[West Bengal]], India<ref name=\"myneta\">{{cite web|url=http://myneta.info/westbengal2011/candidate.php?candidate_id=381|title=Dilip Ghosh (\u09ad\u09be\u09b0\u09a4\u09c0\u09af\u09bc \u099c\u09a8\u09a4\u09be \u09aa\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u099f\u09bf (BJP)) |publisher=myneta.info|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref>\n| residence     = [[Kolkata]]\n| successor     = \n| party         = [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n| otherparty    = [[Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh]]\n| website = {{url|dilipghosh.online}} \n}}\n\n'''Dilip Ghosh''' (born 1 August, 1964) is an Indian politician from West Bengal. He is the incumbent [[Member of parliament (India)|Member of Parliament]] representing the [[Medinipur (Lok Sabha constituency)|Medinipur constituency]] in [[Lok Sabha]] and also currently serving as the president of the [[West Bengal]] unit of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]].<ref name=\"hindu\">{{cite news |agency=[[Press Trust of India|PTI]] |title=Dilip Ghosh appointed West Bengal BJP chief. |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/dilip-ghosh-appointed-west-bengal-bjp-chief/article7976954.ece|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=11 December 2015|accessdate=20 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Dilip Ghosh WB BJP president |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/bjp-appoints-rss-man-dilip-ghosh-as-new-party-chief-in-west-bengal/story-p5FIaccmwytlnpolmcvESN.html|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/amid-row-over-like-dogs-remark-dilip-ghosh-re-named-bengal-bjp-chief-2164949 | title=Dilip Ghosh Re-Named Bengal BJP Chief Amid Row over \"Like Dogs\" Remark|publisher =NDTV|date =January 16, 2020|first1=Monideepa|last1= Banerjie|first2=Anindita |last2=Sanyal}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/dilip-ghosh-re-elected-west-bengal-bjp-chief/article30578888.ece |title = Dilip Ghosh re-elected West Bengal BJP chief|newspaper = The Hindu|date = 16 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nGhosh held charge of the [[Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh]] in [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]], before joining the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] in 2014. In 2016, he was elected as the Member of the West Bengal Legislative Assembly from [[Kharagpur Sadar (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Kharagpur Sadar]], defeating former [[Speaker (politics)|speaker]] [[Gyan Singh Sohanpal]] of [[Indian National Congress]].\n\n==Early life==\nGhosh was born into a Bengali Yadav family at Kuliana village near [[Gopiballavpur]] of [[Paschim Medinipur district]], [[West Bengal]] on 1 August 1964. He was the second of the four sons of Bholanath Ghosh and Puspalata Ghosh.\n\nAfter completing his secondary schooling, Ghosh claims to have pursued [[Diploma in Engineering|diploma in engineering]] from a polytechnic college in [[Jhargram]] over an affidavit filed with the [[Election Commission of India]]; however the lone polytechnic institute in the region \u2013 [[Ishwar Chandra Vidyasagar Polytechnic]] has since denied the claims over a [[Right to Information Act, 2005|RTI]] reply.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/kolkata/rti-reply-contradicts-bjp-bengal-president-s-education-qualification-claims/story-z8FMi8vkSYVWJHX1WqnMIL.html|title=RTI reply contradicts BJP Bengal president's education qualification claims|date=2017-04-08|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-rti-reply-reveals-bjp-s-dilip-ghosh-lied-about-education-in-poll-affidavit-2389371|title=RTI reveals BJP Bengal chief Dilip Ghosh gave incorrect info about education in poll affidavit|last=Ali|first=Arshad|date=2017-04-08|website=DNA India|language=en|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/kolkata/fake-educational-credentials-ex-bjp-leader-moves-hc-against-dilip-ghosh-4637947/|title=Fake Educational Credentials: Ex-BJP leader moves HC against Dilip Ghosh|date=2017-05-03|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref>\n\nIn 1984, he formally joined [[Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh]] (RSS), an Indian [[Right-wing politics|right-wing]], [[Hindu nationalism|Hindu nationalist]] organisation as a volunteer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oneindia.com/politicians/dilip-ghosh-9209.html|title=Dilip Ghosh|access-date=March 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Political career==\n===Early Political Career===\nGhosh started his political journey as a \u201cPracharak\u201d of RSS in 1984.He was the in-charge of RSS in [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]] from 1999 to 2007, and worked as an assistant to former RSS chief [[K. S. Sudarshan]]. In 2014, Ghosh was loaned into BJP<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=PoxmDwAAQBAJ|title=The RSS: A View to the Inside|last=Andersen|first=Walter|last2=Damle|first2=Shridhar|date=2018-08-17|publisher=Penguin Random House India Private Limited|isbn=978-93-5305-159-4|location=|pages=149|language=en}}</ref> and was appointed as the General Secretary of the West Bengal unit. In 2015, Ghosh was appointed as West Bengal State President of the BJP.<ref>{{cite news |title=BJP declares Dilip Ghosh as new WB state president |url=http://www.anandabazar.com/state/bjp-declares-dilip-ghosh-as-new-wb-state-president-dgtl-1.259845|work=[[Anandabazar Patrika]]|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nGhosh started his electoral debut in [[2016 West Bengal Legislative Assembly election|2016]] contesting the [[West Bengal Legislative Assembly]] from [[Kharagpur Sadar]],He won in the [[Kharagpur Sadar]] constituency of [[Paschim Medinipur]] district by defeating his nearest rival [[Gyan Singh Sohanpal]], an [[Indian National Congress]] candidate. Gyan Singh Sohanpal of Congress had won the Kharagpur Sadar assembly seat seven times in a row from 1982 to 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/elections/west-bengal/kharagpur-sadar-mla-results|title=KHARAGPUR SADAR Election Result 2016, Winner, KHARAGPUR SADAR MLA, West Bengal|website=NDTV.com|accessdate=7 April 2019}}</ref> \n\nIn September 2016, Ghosh went on a BJP-sponsored seven-day trip to USA, to highlight \"oppression\" of the [[Hindus]] in West Bengal and infiltration of [[Muslim]]s from [[Bangladesh]]; other speakers in the programme were [[Subramanian Swamy]] and [[Hukum Singh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/kolkata/bjp-state-chief-to-highlight-plight-of-bengal-hindus-in-the-us/story-gk97svcpNwPTLwBCBaxGbM.html|title=BJP state chief to highlight plight of Bengal Hindus in the US|date=25 August 2016|website=Hindustan Times |accessdate=7 April 2019}}</ref> \n\nGhosh won the [[Medinipur (Lok Sabha constituency)|Medinipur Lok Sabha constituency]] in the [[2019 Indian general election|2019 Lok Sabha General Elections]] by a margin of 88,952 votes and a vote share of 48.62% by defeating Trinamool Congress candidate [[Manas Bhunia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://results.eci.gov.in/pc/en/constituencywise/ConstituencywiseS2534.htm?ac=34|title=General Election 2019 - Election Commission of India|website=results.eci.gov.in|access-date=2019-08-31}}</ref>In August 2019, Ghosh accompanied [[Ram Nath Kovind|Ramnath Kovind]] to an official seven-day visit to the African countries of [[Benin]], [[The Gambia]] and [[Guinea]] as a part of the official Indian delegation, which also consisted of [[Pratap Chandra Sarangi]], the [[Minister of State (India)|Minister of State in the Government of India]] for [[Ministry of Animal Husbandry, Dairying and Fisheries|Animal Husbandry, Dairying and Fisheries]] and [[Ministry of Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises|Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/president-ram-nath-kovind-departs-for-official-seven-day-visit-to-africa-mos-pratap-chandra-sarangi-mp-dilip-ghosh-accompany-7069291.html|title=President Ram Nath Kovind departs for official seven-day visit to Africa; MoS Pratap Chandra Sarangi, MP Dilip Ghosh accompany|website=Firstpost|access-date=2019-08-31}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020 Dilip Ghosh  was re-appointed as West Bengal BJP president.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://m.economictimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/dilip-ghosh-re-elected-as-west-bengal-bjp-president/videoshow/73293674.cms|publisher=Economics Times|date=16 Jan 2020|title =Dilip Ghosh re-elected as West Bengal BJP president}} </ref>\n\n==Positions Held ==\n===Elected Offices===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! colspan = \"2\" |Year\n! Description\n|-\n|colspan = \"2\" bgcolor = \"black\" |{{color|white|May, 2019-incumbent}} \n|bgcolor = \"black\" | {{color|yellow|Member of Parliament, Lok Sabha}} {{color|white|(1st term) - }} {{color|yellow|Medinipur}}\n|-\n|bgcolor = \"black\" |\n|24 July 2019\n|Member, Committee on Estimates\n|-\n|bgcolor = \"black\" |\n|13 September 2019\n|Member, Standing Committee on Home Affairs\n|-\n|bgcolor = \"black\" |\n|09 October 2019\n|Member, Committee of Privileges\n|-\n|bgcolor = \"black\" |\n|\n|Member, Consultative Committee, Ministry of Skill Development and Entrepreneurship\n|-\n|colspan = \"2\" bgcolor = \"black\" |{{color|white|2016-2019}} \n|bgcolor = \"black\" |{{color|yellow|Member, West Bengal Legislative Assembly}} {{color|white|(1st term) - }} {{color|yellow|Kharagpur}}\n|-\n|bgcolor = \"black\" |\n|2018-2019\n| \n*Member, Transport Committee, West Bengal Legislative Assembly\n*Member, Library Committee, West Bengal Legislative Assembly\n|-\n|}\n\n===Executive Offices===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Description\n|-\n| colspan = \"2\" bgcolor = \"red\" | {{color|white|None}} \n|} \n===Political Offices===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Description\n! Party/Organization \n|-\n| bgcolor = dark orange|{{color|white|2020 - incumbent}} \n| rowspan = \"2\" bgcolor = dark orange|{{color|white|President, West Bengal}} \n| rowspan = \"3\" bgcolor = dark orange|[[Bharatiya Janata Party|{{color|white|BJP}}]] \n|-\n| bgcolor = dark orange|{{color|white|2014 - 2020}} \n|-\n| bgcolor = dark orange|{{color|white|2014-2015}} \n| bgcolor = dark orange|{{color|white|General Secretary, West Bengal}}  \n|-\n|1999-2007\n| In-Charge,Andaman and Nicobar Islands\n| RSS\n|-\n|}\n\n==Controversies==\nHe is known for his intemperate language and repeated calls to violence.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://thewire.in/politics/dilip-ghosh-bengal-bjp |title = Can Dilip Ghosh's Foul Rhetoric Make Inroads with Bengal's Bhadralok Gentry?}}</ref> In May 2016, he raised a controversy when he said girl students of [[Jadavpur University]] \"below standard and shameless who are always in search of opportunity to be in the company of male students\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.timesofindia.com/city/kolkata/Jadavpur-University-girl-students-shameless-below-standard-BJP-leader-Dilip-Ghosh/amp_articleshow/52271663.cms | title=Jadavpur University girl students 'shameless', 'below standard': BJP leader Dilip Ghosh - Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/west-bengal-kolkata-dilip-ghosh-remark-on-ju-girls-congress-supporters-demand-apology-2802444/ |title = Dilip Ghosh remark on JU girls, Congress supporters demand apology|date = 16 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india/jadavpur-university-women-students-are-shameless-bjp-s-dilip-ghosh/story-5Hgu6jVQlL1LGaUSWNpDrJ.html |title = Jadavpur University women students are 'shameless': BJP's Dilip Ghosh|date = 16 May 2016}}</ref> In August 2019, he declared that the [[Trinamul Congress]] workers\u2019 families would be wiped out if he would start killing them. Triggering controversy, he even ordered his party workers rather to take revenge against [[Trinamul Congress|TMC]] and even the police through violence.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.asianage.com/metros/kolkata/280819/dilip-ghosh-threatens-to-kill-tmc-workers-kin.html |title = Dilip Ghosh threatens to kill TMC workers' kin|date = 28 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/bash-up-tmc-workers-cops-bjp-bengal-chief-to-party-workers-1592245-2019-08-27 |title = Bash up TMC workers, cops: BJP Bengal chief to party workers}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.dailypioneer.com/2019/india/bengal-bjp-chief-threatens-tmc-with----mass-murder---.html |title = Bengal BJP chief threatens TMC with 'mass murder'}}</ref> In September 2019, terming the Left and ultra-Left students of [[Jadavpur University]] \u201canti-nationals\" and \"terrorists\", he insinuated that his party would conduct a \u201cBalakot-like surgical strike\u201d on the JU campus to \u201cdrive out the communists\u201d.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/west-bengal/wait-for-surgical-strike-on-jadavpur-university-bjp/cid/1706410 |title = Wait for surgical strike on Jadavpur University: BJP}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kolkata/surgical-strike-needed-to-destroy-jadavpur-university-hub-of-anti-nationals-says-bjps-dilip-ghosh/article29469741.ece/amp/ |title = Jadavpur University, a hub of anti-nationals, will be destroyed in a Balakot-like surgical strike: BJP's Dilip Ghosh|newspaper = The Hindu|date = 20 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://amp.scroll.in/latest/937965/kolkata-bjp-marches-in-protest-against-alleged-assault-on-babul-supriyo-at-jadavpur-university |title = West Bengal BJP chief says surgical strike in JU will destroy groups that assaulted Babul Supriyo}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.india.com/news/india/ju-a-hub-of-anti-national-activities-our-cadres-will-conduct-surgical-strike-to-destroy-them-dilip-ghosh-3779317/amp/ | title='JU a Hub of Anti-national Activities, Our Cadres Will Conduct Surgical Strike to Destroy Them': Dilip Ghosh| date=20 September 2019}}</ref> In November 2019, he stirred up a controversy with his remark stating that foreign cows are aunties, Indian cows produce gold. \u201cThe characteristics of Indian cows is that its milk has gold which is why its colour is yellow to some extent. \u201cThe Indian cows have hump. But the foreign cows do not have it,\u201d he said while addressing a gathering at an event Gopa Ashtami Karyakram organised by him and Gavikalyan Samity at [[Burdwan]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.asianage.com/metros/kolkata/061119/eat-dog-meat-also-bjp-chief-tells-beef-eating-intellectuals.html | title=Foreign cows are aunties, Indian cows produce gold: Dilip Ghosh| date=6 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/gaumatas-milk-has-gold-foreign-cow-breeds-are-aunties-bjp-neta/amp_articleshow/71931240.cms |title = Gaumata's milk has gold, foreign cow breeds are aunties: BJP neta - Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.theweek.in/news/india/2019/11/05/bengal-bjp-chief-calls-foreign-cow-aunties-asks-beef-eaters-to-eat-dog.html | title=Bengal BJP chief calls foreign cows 'aunties', asks beef eaters to eat dog}}</ref> He also courted controversy when he attacked \"few intellectuals\" for having beef on roads and asked them to consume 'dog meat' at their homes.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/foreign-cows-are-aunties-indian-cows-have-gold-in-their-milk-bjps-dilip-ghosh20191105120607/ |title = Foreign cows are 'aunties', Indian cows have gold in their milk: BJP's Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-few-intellectuals-eat-beef-on-roads-but-bjp-s-dilip-ghosh-bizarre-remark-2800204/amp |title = 'Few intellectuals eat beef on roads but...': BJP's Dilip Ghosh bizarre remark}}</ref> In December 2019, he was embroiled in a controversy when he said his\u00a0party allows people to create trouble because the media looks for news.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/we-allow-people-to-create-trouble-bengal-bjp-leader-sets-up-new-controversy/story-e2picZ48bl10T720UuAFlL.html |title = 'We allow people to create trouble': Bengal BJP leader sets up new controversy|date = 27 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news18.com/amp/news/politics/if-tmc-creates-trouble-we-will-also-follow-suit-bjps-dilip-ghosh-courts-new-controversy-2437783.html | title='If TMC Creates Trouble, We Will Also Follow Suit': BJP's Dilip Ghosh Courts New Controversy}}</ref> He drew criticism when he turned away an ambulance which tried to make way through a rally he was addressing in [[Nadia]].<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/dilip-ghosh-turns-away-ambulance-during-rally-in-west-bengal-120010800183_1.html |title = Dilip Ghosh turns away ambulance during rally in West Bengal|newspaper = Business Standard India|date = 8 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/politics/dilip-ghosh-turns-away-ambulance-during-rally-in-west-bengal20200108082249/ |title = Dilip Ghosh turns away ambulance during rally in West Bengal}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/find-another-route-bengal-bjp-chief-dilip-ghosh-turns-away-ambulance-as-rally-blocks-road-watch-2450397.html |title = 'Find Another Route': Bengal BJP Chief Dilip Ghosh Turns Away Ambulance as Rally Blocks Road &#124; Watch}}</ref> While the ambulance was actually carrying a patient.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.scoopwhoop.com/news/bjp-mp-dilip-ghosh-under-fire-for-turning-ambulance-away-during-rally-in-bengal/ |title = BJP MP Dilip Ghosh Under Fire for Turning Ambulance Away During Rally in Bengal|date = 8 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.northeasttoday.in/defiant-bjp-bengal-chief-blocks-ambulance-during-rally-later-says-dont-have-faltu-time-to-discuss-issue/ |title = Defiant BJP Bengal chief blocks ambulance during rally, later says 'don't have faltu time' to discuss issue \u00bb Northeast Today|date = 8 January 2020}}</ref> He claimed that \" [[Trinamool Congress|TMC]] are doing it purposely. It is their tactic to disrupt the rally\". On January 2020, he again raised controversy by remarking that [[West Bengal]] has turned into hub of anti-nationals.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/bengal-turned-into-hub-of-anti-nationals-under-tmc-regime-dilip-ghosh/amp_articleshow/73256985.cms |title = Bengal turned into hub of anti-nationals under TMC regime: Dilip Ghosh - Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2020/jan/15/west-bengal-turned-into-hub-of-anti-nationals-under-tmc-regime-dilip-ghosh-2089561.html |title = West Bengal turned into hub of anti-nationals under TMC regime: Dilip Ghosh}}</ref> He also courted controversy when he said anti [[Citizenship (Amendment) Act, 2019|CAA]] intellectuals are 'devils' and 'parasites' who don't know about their parents.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/now-dilip-ghosh-calls-anti-caa-intellectuals-parasites-who-dont-know-about-their-parents-2462803.html | title=Now, Dilip Ghosh Calls Anti-CAA Intellectuals 'Parasites Who Don't Know About Their Parents'}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/west-bengal/parentage-jibe-from-dilip-ghosh/cid/1736777 | title=Parentage jibe from Dilip}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/bengal-bjps-dilip-ghosh-on-caa-protests-intellectuals-opposing-law-parasites-2165999 |title = Intellectuals at Citizenship Law Protests \"Parasites\": Bengal BJP Chief Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/intellectuals-opposing-caa-are-devils-parasites-says-dilip-ghosh-day-after-being-re-elected-as-west-bengal-bjp-chief-7925611.html |title = 'Intellectuals opposing CAA are devils, parasites,' says Dilip Ghosh, day after being re-elected as West Bengal BJP chief}}</ref> On January 28, 2020, he raised another controversy when he questioned why nobody was dying at the [[Shaheen Bagh protests]]\nagainst the [[Citizenship Amendment Act]] when several people had lost their lives waiting to withdraw money from banks during the [[2016 Indian banknote demonetisation|demonetisation]] initiative over three years ago. \"What surprises me is that people were dying after standing in line for two to three hours. But now women and children are sitting in temperatures as low as 4-5 degrees Celsius but nobody is dying! What nectar did they have? I am astonished! What is their incentive (for staying alive)?\" he said at an event organised by the Kolkata Press Club.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news18.com/amp/news/politics/why-no-shaheen-bagh-protester-falling-ill-wonders-dilip-ghosh-2477245.html |title = Why Has No Protester at Shaheen Bagh Fallen Ill or Died Until Now, Asks BJP MP Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/citizenship-amendment-act-bjps-dilip-ghosh-says-many-died-in-notes-ban-queues-why-not-shaheen-bagh-2171141?amp=1&akamai-rum=off | title=\"If 100 Died in Notes Ban Queues, Why Not Shaheen Bagh?\": Shocker by BJP's Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/why-no-shaheen-bagh-protester-falling-ill-wonders-bengal-bjp-chief-dilip-ghosh/1838028/?utm_campaign | title=Why no Shaheen Bagh protester falling ill, wonders Bengal BJP chief Dilip Ghosh| date=28 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/video/why-shaheen-bagh-protester-falling-despite-chilly-winter-dilip-ghosh-1641208-2020-01-29 |title = Why no Shaheen Bagh protester falling ill despite chilly winter: Dilip Ghosh}}</ref> On January 30, he courted yet another controversy with his remark stating that, \"Unless you visit jail, you cannot be a political leader\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news18.com/news/politics/unless-you-visit-jail-you-cannot-be-a-leader-bengal-bjp-chief-dilip-ghosh-tells-partymen-2479747.html | title=Unless You Visit Jail, You Cannot be a Leader: Bengal BJP Chief Dilip Ghosh Tells Partymen}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/dilip-ghosh-to-bjp-workers-cannot-be-a-leader-unless-you-go-to-jail-2172160 |title = \"Can't be a Leader Unless You Go to Jail\": Dilip Ghosh to BJP Workers}}</ref> His comments drew widespread criticism from opposition parties when a lone woman carrying anti [[Citizenship Amendment Act|CAA]] poster was heckled by his partyman. Later while speaking to newsmen, Ghosh justified the heckling of the woman saying \"Our men did the right thing. She should thank her stars that she was only heckled and nothing else was done to her\".<ref>{{cite news |title=should-thank-her-stars-nothing-else-done-dilip-ghosh-to-anti-caa-protester-heckled-by-bjp-cadres- |url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/should-thank-her-stars-nothing-else-done-dilip-ghosh-to-anti-caa-protester-heckled-by-bjp-cadres-2480201.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.sangbadpratidin.in/kolkata/state-bjp-president-dilip-ghosh-attacks-a-lady-in-patuli/ | title=State BJP president Dilip Ghosh attacks a lady in Patuli| date=30 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://eisamay.indiatimes.com/west-bengal-news/kolkata-news/controversial-comment-of-west-bengal-bjp-president-dilip-ghosh-about-a-lady-who-protested-against-caa-npr-during-bjps-pro-caa-abhinandan-rally/amp_articleshow/73775423.cms |title = Dilip Ghosh: BJP-\u09b0 \u09ae\u09bf\u099b\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7 \u098f\u0995\u09b2\u09be \u09a4\u09b0\u09c1\u09a3\u09c0\u09b0 CAA-\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09bf\u09ac\u09be\u09a6, '\u0993 \u0995\u09bf \u09b6\u09b9\u09bf\u09a6 \u09b9\u09a4\u09c7 \u099a\u09be\u09af\u09bc?' \u09ab\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ac\u09cb\u09ae\u09be \u09a6\u09bf\u09b2\u09c0\u09aa\u09c7\u09b0 - controversial comment of west bengal BJP president dilip ghosh about a lady who protested against caa-NPR during BJP's pro-caa abhinandan rally &#124; Eisamay}}</ref> On February 16, he raked up yet another controversy with his remark on anti [[Citizenship Amendment Act|CAA]] protesters. He said, \"some uneducated, unaware, poor people have been lured with money and are being fed [[Biryani]] with foreign funds to continue with the protests.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/biryani-foreign-funds-driving-the-uneducated-to-caa-rallies-bengal-bjp-president-dilip-ghosh/amp_articleshow/74155796.cms\n|title = Biryani, foreign funds driving the uneducated to CAA rallies: Bengal BJP president Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/protesters-at-delhis-shaheen-bagh-kolkatas-park-circus-uneducated-and-poor-doing-it-for-money-says-bengal-bjp-chief-dilip-ghosh-8045921.html\n|title = Protesters at Delhi's Shaheen Bagh, Kolkata's Park Circus 'uneducated' and 'poor', doing it for money, says Bengal BJP chief Dilip Ghosh}}</ref> On March 11, he claimed that, \"Corona attacks only by staying away from nature, we who live with nature do not have this disease,\" he added, \"To avoid corona, people should dry their clothes in sunlight for 2 hours, which kills the [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|Coronavirus]].\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=\nhttps://zeenews.india.com/india/bjp-mp-dilip-ghosh-suggests-people-living-with-nature-do-not-get-coronavirus-2268912.html|title = Dilip Ghosh suggests people living close to nature do not Coronavirus}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url= https://www.deccanherald.com/amp/national/east-and-northeast/we-are-not-scared-have-gods-blessings-bjps-dilip-ghosh-downplays-coronavirus-threat-812604.html|title = We are not scared, have god's blessings: BJP's Dilip Ghosh downplays coronavirus threat}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=\nhttps://www.thequint.com/news/india/have-gods-blessings-bjp-dilip-ghosh-downplays-coronavirus-threat|title =  Have God\u2019s Blessing\u2019: BJP\u2019s Dilip Ghosh Downplays COVID-19 Threat}}</ref>On March 16, he again claimed that, there is no harm in drinking [[cow urine]] and he has no qualms in admitting he consumes it. He said that, \"For ages, people in our country have consumed urine, all of them have been fit and fine. I have no qualm in accepting that I consume [[Cow Urine]] and will again do so\".The claim that consumption of cow urine can cure coronavirus drew sharp criticism from the ruling [[Trinamool Congress]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/india/story/i-consume-cow-urine-people-have-done-so-for-ages-bjp-west-bengal-chief-dilip-ghosh-1656683-2020-03-18#referrer=https://www.google.com|title= I consume cow urine, people have done so for ages: BJP West Bengal chief Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/east-and-northeast/bengal-bjp-chief-dilip-ghosh-says-no-harm-in-drinking-cow-urine-party-mp-says-time-to-shun-unscientific-beliefs-814873.html| title= Bengal BJP chief Dilip Ghosh says no harm in drinking cow urine; party MP says time to shun 'unscientific beliefs\"\n}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.bjpbengal.org BJP Bengal &#124; Bhartiya Janta Party]\n*[https://www.oheyo.com/bjp-west-bengal BJP Bengal | Video Question and Answer] on [https://www.oheyo.com/ Oheyo]\n\n{{17th Lok Sabha members from all states}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ghosh, Dilip}}\n[[Category:Bengali people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Kolkata]]\n[[Category:Bharatiya Janata Party politicians from West Bengal]]\n[[Category:Bengali Hindus]]\n[[Category:Members of the West Bengal Legislative Assembly]]\n[[Category:Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh members]]\n[[Category:17th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:State Presidents of Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n\n<br />{{short description|Indian Member of Parliament}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name          = Dilip Ghosh\n| image         = Dilip Ghosh MP.jpg\n| image_size    = 200px\n| caption       = \n| office1       = [[Member of Parliament (India)|Member of Parliament]], [[Lok Sabha]]\n| constituency1 = [[Medinipur (Lok Sabha constituency)|Medinipur]]\n| term_start1   = 23 May 2019\n| term_end1     = \n| predecessor1  = [[Sandhya Roy]]\n| successor1    = \n| office3       = [[Bharatiya Janata Party, West Bengal|9th President of Bharatiya Janata Party - West Bengal]] \n| assembly      = [[Member of Legislative Assembly|Member of West Bengal Legislative Assembly]]\n| term_start3   = 2015\n| term_end3     = \n| predecessor3  = Rahul Sinha\n| office2       = [[Member of Legislative Assembly|Member of West Bengal Legislative Assembly]]\n| constituency2 = [[Kharagpur Sadar (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Kharagpur Sadar]]\n| term_start2   = 2016\n| term_end2     = 23 May 2019\n| predecessor2  = [[Gyan Singh Sohanpal]]\n| successor2    = [[Pradip Sarkar]]\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age | 1 August 1964 |df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[Jhargram district|Kuliana]], [[West Bengal]], India<ref name=\"myneta\">{{cite web|url=http://myneta.info/westbengal2011/candidate.php?candidate_id=381|title=Dilip Ghosh (\u09ad\u09be\u09b0\u09a4\u09c0\u09af\u09bc \u099c\u09a8\u09a4\u09be \u09aa\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u099f\u09bf (BJP)) |publisher=myneta.info|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref>\n| residence     = [[Kolkata]]\n| successor     = \n| party         = [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n| otherparty    = [[Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh]]\n| website = {{url|dilipghosh.online}} \n}}\n\n'''Dilip Ghosh''' (born 1 August, 1964) is an Indian politician from West Bengal. He is the incumbent [[Member of parliament (India)|Member of Parliament]] representing the [[Medinipur (Lok Sabha constituency)|Medinipur constituency]] in [[Lok Sabha]] and also currently serving as the president of the [[West Bengal]] unit of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]].<ref name=\"hindu\">{{cite news |agency=[[Press Trust of India|PTI]] |title=Dilip Ghosh appointed West Bengal BJP chief. |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/dilip-ghosh-appointed-west-bengal-bjp-chief/article7976954.ece|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|date=11 December 2015|accessdate=20 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Dilip Ghosh WB BJP president |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/bjp-appoints-rss-man-dilip-ghosh-as-new-party-chief-in-west-bengal/story-p5FIaccmwytlnpolmcvESN.html|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/amid-row-over-like-dogs-remark-dilip-ghosh-re-named-bengal-bjp-chief-2164949 | title=Dilip Ghosh Re-Named Bengal BJP Chief Amid Row over \"Like Dogs\" Remark|publisher =NDTV|date =January 16, 2020|first1=Monideepa|last1= Banerjie|first2=Anindita |last2=Sanyal}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/dilip-ghosh-re-elected-west-bengal-bjp-chief/article30578888.ece |title = Dilip Ghosh re-elected West Bengal BJP chief|newspaper = The Hindu|date = 16 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nGhosh held charge of the [[Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh]] in [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]], before joining the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] in 2014. In 2016, he was elected as the Member of the West Bengal Legislative Assembly from [[Kharagpur Sadar (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Kharagpur Sadar]], defeating former [[Speaker (politics)|speaker]] [[Gyan Singh Sohanpal]] of [[Indian National Congress]]. Ghosh encourages the youth leaders of Bengal. He once said, \"we need more youth leaders like Joydip Banerjee from Durgapur, Sambaran Bose from Kalna etc. We will blend the power of youth and brain of experienced personnel to be the strongest, sharpest and mightiest.\" \n\n==Early life==\nGhosh was born into a Bengali Yadav family at Kuliana village near [[Gopiballavpur]] of [[Paschim Medinipur district]], [[West Bengal]] on 1 August 1964. He was the second of the four sons of Bholanath Ghosh and Puspalata Ghosh.\n\nAfter completing his secondary schooling, Ghosh claims to have pursued [[Diploma in Engineering|diploma in engineering]] from a polytechnic college in [[Jhargram]] over an affidavit filed with the [[Election Commission of India]]; however the lone polytechnic institute in the region \u2013 [[Ishwar Chandra Vidyasagar Polytechnic]] has since denied the claims over a [[Right to Information Act, 2005|RTI]] reply.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/kolkata/rti-reply-contradicts-bjp-bengal-president-s-education-qualification-claims/story-z8FMi8vkSYVWJHX1WqnMIL.html|title=RTI reply contradicts BJP Bengal president's education qualification claims|date=2017-04-08|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-rti-reply-reveals-bjp-s-dilip-ghosh-lied-about-education-in-poll-affidavit-2389371|title=RTI reveals BJP Bengal chief Dilip Ghosh gave incorrect info about education in poll affidavit|last=Ali|first=Arshad|date=2017-04-08|website=DNA India|language=en|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/kolkata/fake-educational-credentials-ex-bjp-leader-moves-hc-against-dilip-ghosh-4637947/|title=Fake Educational Credentials: Ex-BJP leader moves HC against Dilip Ghosh|date=2017-05-03|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref>\n\nIn 1984, he formally joined [[Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh]] (RSS), an Indian [[Right-wing politics|right-wing]], [[Hindu nationalism|Hindu nationalist]] organisation as a volunteer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oneindia.com/politicians/dilip-ghosh-9209.html|title=Dilip Ghosh|access-date=March 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Political career==\n===Early Political Career===\nGhosh started his political journey as a \u201cPracharak\u201d of RSS in 1984.He was the in-charge of RSS in [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]] from 1999 to 2007, and worked as an assistant to former RSS chief [[K. S. Sudarshan]]. In 2014, Ghosh was loaned into BJP<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=PoxmDwAAQBAJ|title=The RSS: A View to the Inside|last=Andersen|first=Walter|last2=Damle|first2=Shridhar|date=2018-08-17|publisher=Penguin Random House India Private Limited|isbn=978-93-5305-159-4|location=|pages=149|language=en}}</ref> and was appointed as the General Secretary of the West Bengal unit. In 2015, Ghosh was appointed as West Bengal State President of the BJP.<ref>{{cite news |title=BJP declares Dilip Ghosh as new WB state president |url=http://www.anandabazar.com/state/bjp-declares-dilip-ghosh-as-new-wb-state-president-dgtl-1.259845|work=[[Anandabazar Patrika]]|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nGhosh started his electoral debut in [[2016 West Bengal Legislative Assembly election|2016]] contesting the [[West Bengal Legislative Assembly]] from [[Kharagpur Sadar]],He won in the [[Kharagpur Sadar]] constituency of [[Paschim Medinipur]] district by defeating his nearest rival [[Gyan Singh Sohanpal]], an [[Indian National Congress]] candidate. Gyan Singh Sohanpal of Congress had won the Kharagpur Sadar assembly seat seven times in a row from 1982 to 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/elections/west-bengal/kharagpur-sadar-mla-results|title=KHARAGPUR SADAR Election Result 2016, Winner, KHARAGPUR SADAR MLA, West Bengal|website=NDTV.com|accessdate=7 April 2019}}</ref> \n\nIn September 2016, Ghosh went on a BJP-sponsored seven-day trip to USA, to highlight \"oppression\" of the [[Hindus]] in West Bengal and infiltration of [[Muslim]]s from [[Bangladesh]]; other speakers in the programme were [[Subramanian Swamy]] and [[Hukum Singh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/kolkata/bjp-state-chief-to-highlight-plight-of-bengal-hindus-in-the-us/story-gk97svcpNwPTLwBCBaxGbM.html|title=BJP state chief to highlight plight of Bengal Hindus in the US|date=25 August 2016|website=Hindustan Times |accessdate=7 April 2019}}</ref> \n\nGhosh won the [[Medinipur (Lok Sabha constituency)|Medinipur Lok Sabha constituency]] in the [[2019 Indian general election|2019 Lok Sabha General Elections]] by a margin of 88,952 votes and a vote share of 48.62% by defeating Trinamool Congress candidate [[Manas Bhunia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://results.eci.gov.in/pc/en/constituencywise/ConstituencywiseS2534.htm?ac=34|title=General Election 2019 - Election Commission of India|website=results.eci.gov.in|access-date=2019-08-31}}</ref>In August 2019, Ghosh accompanied [[Ram Nath Kovind|Ramnath Kovind]] to an official seven-day visit to the African countries of [[Benin]], [[The Gambia]] and [[Guinea]] as a part of the official Indian delegation, which also consisted of [[Pratap Chandra Sarangi]], the [[Minister of State (India)|Minister of State in the Government of India]] for [[Ministry of Animal Husbandry, Dairying and Fisheries|Animal Husbandry, Dairying and Fisheries]] and [[Ministry of Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises|Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/president-ram-nath-kovind-departs-for-official-seven-day-visit-to-africa-mos-pratap-chandra-sarangi-mp-dilip-ghosh-accompany-7069291.html|title=President Ram Nath Kovind departs for official seven-day visit to Africa; MoS Pratap Chandra Sarangi, MP Dilip Ghosh accompany|website=Firstpost|access-date=2019-08-31}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020 Dilip Ghosh  was re-appointed as West Bengal BJP president.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://m.economictimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/dilip-ghosh-re-elected-as-west-bengal-bjp-president/videoshow/73293674.cms|publisher=Economics Times|date=16 Jan 2020|title =Dilip Ghosh re-elected as West Bengal BJP president}} </ref>\n\n==Positions Held ==\n===Elected Offices===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! colspan = \"2\" |Year\n! Description\n|-\n|colspan = \"2\" bgcolor = \"black\" |{{color|white|May, 2019-incumbent}} \n|bgcolor = \"black\" | {{color|yellow|Member of Parliament, Lok Sabha}} {{color|white|(1st term) - }} {{color|yellow|Medinipur}}\n|-\n|bgcolor = \"black\" |\n|24 July 2019\n|Member, Committee on Estimates\n|-\n|bgcolor = \"black\" |\n|13 September 2019\n|Member, Standing Committee on Home Affairs\n|-\n|bgcolor = \"black\" |\n|09 October 2019\n|Member, Committee of Privileges\n|-\n|bgcolor = \"black\" |\n|\n|Member, Consultative Committee, Ministry of Skill Development and Entrepreneurship\n|-\n|colspan = \"2\" bgcolor = \"black\" |{{color|white|2016-2019}} \n|bgcolor = \"black\" |{{color|yellow|Member, West Bengal Legislative Assembly}} {{color|white|(1st term) - }} {{color|yellow|Kharagpur}}\n|-\n|bgcolor = \"black\" |\n|2018-2019\n| \n*Member, Transport Committee, West Bengal Legislative Assembly\n*Member, Library Committee, West Bengal Legislative Assembly\n|-\n|}\n\n===Executive Offices===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Description\n|-\n| colspan = \"2\" bgcolor = \"red\" | {{color|white|None}} \n|} \n===Political Offices===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Description\n! Party/Organization \n|-\n| bgcolor = dark orange|{{color|white|2020 - incumbent}} \n| rowspan = \"2\" bgcolor = dark orange|{{color|white|President, West Bengal}} \n| rowspan = \"3\" bgcolor = dark orange|[[Bharatiya Janata Party|{{color|white|BJP}}]] \n|-\n| bgcolor = dark orange|{{color|white|2014 - 2020}} \n|-\n| bgcolor = dark orange|{{color|white|2014-2015}} \n| bgcolor = dark orange|{{color|white|General Secretary, West Bengal}}  \n|-\n|1999-2007\n| In-Charge,Andaman and Nicobar Islands\n| RSS\n|-\n|}\n\n==Controversies==\nHe is known for his intemperate language and repeated calls to violence.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://thewire.in/politics/dilip-ghosh-bengal-bjp |title = Can Dilip Ghosh's Foul Rhetoric Make Inroads with Bengal's Bhadralok Gentry?}}</ref> In May 2016, he raised a controversy when he said girl students of [[Jadavpur University]] \"below standard and shameless who are always in search of opportunity to be in the company of male students\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.timesofindia.com/city/kolkata/Jadavpur-University-girl-students-shameless-below-standard-BJP-leader-Dilip-Ghosh/amp_articleshow/52271663.cms | title=Jadavpur University girl students 'shameless', 'below standard': BJP leader Dilip Ghosh - Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/west-bengal-kolkata-dilip-ghosh-remark-on-ju-girls-congress-supporters-demand-apology-2802444/ |title = Dilip Ghosh remark on JU girls, Congress supporters demand apology|date = 16 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india/jadavpur-university-women-students-are-shameless-bjp-s-dilip-ghosh/story-5Hgu6jVQlL1LGaUSWNpDrJ.html |title = Jadavpur University women students are 'shameless': BJP's Dilip Ghosh|date = 16 May 2016}}</ref> In August 2019, he declared that the [[Trinamul Congress]] workers\u2019 families would be wiped out if he would start killing them. Triggering controversy, he even ordered his party workers rather to take revenge against [[Trinamul Congress|TMC]] and even the police through violence.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.asianage.com/metros/kolkata/280819/dilip-ghosh-threatens-to-kill-tmc-workers-kin.html |title = Dilip Ghosh threatens to kill TMC workers' kin|date = 28 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/bash-up-tmc-workers-cops-bjp-bengal-chief-to-party-workers-1592245-2019-08-27 |title = Bash up TMC workers, cops: BJP Bengal chief to party workers}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.dailypioneer.com/2019/india/bengal-bjp-chief-threatens-tmc-with----mass-murder---.html |title = Bengal BJP chief threatens TMC with 'mass murder'}}</ref> In September 2019, terming the Left and ultra-Left students of [[Jadavpur University]] \u201canti-nationals\" and \"terrorists\", he insinuated that his party would conduct a \u201cBalakot-like surgical strike\u201d on the JU campus to \u201cdrive out the communists\u201d.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/west-bengal/wait-for-surgical-strike-on-jadavpur-university-bjp/cid/1706410 |title = Wait for surgical strike on Jadavpur University: BJP}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kolkata/surgical-strike-needed-to-destroy-jadavpur-university-hub-of-anti-nationals-says-bjps-dilip-ghosh/article29469741.ece/amp/ |title = Jadavpur University, a hub of anti-nationals, will be destroyed in a Balakot-like surgical strike: BJP's Dilip Ghosh|newspaper = The Hindu|date = 20 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://amp.scroll.in/latest/937965/kolkata-bjp-marches-in-protest-against-alleged-assault-on-babul-supriyo-at-jadavpur-university |title = West Bengal BJP chief says surgical strike in JU will destroy groups that assaulted Babul Supriyo}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.india.com/news/india/ju-a-hub-of-anti-national-activities-our-cadres-will-conduct-surgical-strike-to-destroy-them-dilip-ghosh-3779317/amp/ | title='JU a Hub of Anti-national Activities, Our Cadres Will Conduct Surgical Strike to Destroy Them': Dilip Ghosh| date=20 September 2019}}</ref> In November 2019, he stirred up a controversy with his remark stating that foreign cows are aunties, Indian cows produce gold. \u201cThe characteristics of Indian cows is that its milk has gold which is why its colour is yellow to some extent. \u201cThe Indian cows have hump. But the foreign cows do not have it,\u201d he said while addressing a gathering at an event Gopa Ashtami Karyakram organised by him and Gavikalyan Samity at [[Burdwan]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.asianage.com/metros/kolkata/061119/eat-dog-meat-also-bjp-chief-tells-beef-eating-intellectuals.html | title=Foreign cows are aunties, Indian cows produce gold: Dilip Ghosh| date=6 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/gaumatas-milk-has-gold-foreign-cow-breeds-are-aunties-bjp-neta/amp_articleshow/71931240.cms |title = Gaumata's milk has gold, foreign cow breeds are aunties: BJP neta - Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.theweek.in/news/india/2019/11/05/bengal-bjp-chief-calls-foreign-cow-aunties-asks-beef-eaters-to-eat-dog.html | title=Bengal BJP chief calls foreign cows 'aunties', asks beef eaters to eat dog}}</ref> He also courted controversy when he attacked \"few intellectuals\" for having beef on roads and asked them to consume 'dog meat' at their homes.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/foreign-cows-are-aunties-indian-cows-have-gold-in-their-milk-bjps-dilip-ghosh20191105120607/ |title = Foreign cows are 'aunties', Indian cows have gold in their milk: BJP's Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-few-intellectuals-eat-beef-on-roads-but-bjp-s-dilip-ghosh-bizarre-remark-2800204/amp |title = 'Few intellectuals eat beef on roads but...': BJP's Dilip Ghosh bizarre remark}}</ref> In December 2019, he was embroiled in a controversy when he said his\u00a0party allows people to create trouble because the media looks for news.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/we-allow-people-to-create-trouble-bengal-bjp-leader-sets-up-new-controversy/story-e2picZ48bl10T720UuAFlL.html |title = 'We allow people to create trouble': Bengal BJP leader sets up new controversy|date = 27 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news18.com/amp/news/politics/if-tmc-creates-trouble-we-will-also-follow-suit-bjps-dilip-ghosh-courts-new-controversy-2437783.html | title='If TMC Creates Trouble, We Will Also Follow Suit': BJP's Dilip Ghosh Courts New Controversy}}</ref> He drew criticism when he turned away an ambulance which tried to make way through a rally he was addressing in [[Nadia]].<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/dilip-ghosh-turns-away-ambulance-during-rally-in-west-bengal-120010800183_1.html |title = Dilip Ghosh turns away ambulance during rally in West Bengal|newspaper = Business Standard India|date = 8 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/politics/dilip-ghosh-turns-away-ambulance-during-rally-in-west-bengal20200108082249/ |title = Dilip Ghosh turns away ambulance during rally in West Bengal}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/find-another-route-bengal-bjp-chief-dilip-ghosh-turns-away-ambulance-as-rally-blocks-road-watch-2450397.html |title = 'Find Another Route': Bengal BJP Chief Dilip Ghosh Turns Away Ambulance as Rally Blocks Road &#124; Watch}}</ref> While the ambulance was actually carrying a patient.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.scoopwhoop.com/news/bjp-mp-dilip-ghosh-under-fire-for-turning-ambulance-away-during-rally-in-bengal/ |title = BJP MP Dilip Ghosh Under Fire for Turning Ambulance Away During Rally in Bengal|date = 8 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.northeasttoday.in/defiant-bjp-bengal-chief-blocks-ambulance-during-rally-later-says-dont-have-faltu-time-to-discuss-issue/ |title = Defiant BJP Bengal chief blocks ambulance during rally, later says 'don't have faltu time' to discuss issue \u00bb Northeast Today|date = 8 January 2020}}</ref> He claimed that \" [[Trinamool Congress|TMC]] are doing it purposely. It is their tactic to disrupt the rally\". On January 2020, he again raised controversy by remarking that [[West Bengal]] has turned into hub of anti-nationals.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/bengal-turned-into-hub-of-anti-nationals-under-tmc-regime-dilip-ghosh/amp_articleshow/73256985.cms |title = Bengal turned into hub of anti-nationals under TMC regime: Dilip Ghosh - Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2020/jan/15/west-bengal-turned-into-hub-of-anti-nationals-under-tmc-regime-dilip-ghosh-2089561.html |title = West Bengal turned into hub of anti-nationals under TMC regime: Dilip Ghosh}}</ref> He also courted controversy when he said anti [[Citizenship (Amendment) Act, 2019|CAA]] intellectuals are 'devils' and 'parasites' who don't know about their parents.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/now-dilip-ghosh-calls-anti-caa-intellectuals-parasites-who-dont-know-about-their-parents-2462803.html | title=Now, Dilip Ghosh Calls Anti-CAA Intellectuals 'Parasites Who Don't Know About Their Parents'}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/west-bengal/parentage-jibe-from-dilip-ghosh/cid/1736777 | title=Parentage jibe from Dilip}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/bengal-bjps-dilip-ghosh-on-caa-protests-intellectuals-opposing-law-parasites-2165999 |title = Intellectuals at Citizenship Law Protests \"Parasites\": Bengal BJP Chief Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/intellectuals-opposing-caa-are-devils-parasites-says-dilip-ghosh-day-after-being-re-elected-as-west-bengal-bjp-chief-7925611.html |title = 'Intellectuals opposing CAA are devils, parasites,' says Dilip Ghosh, day after being re-elected as West Bengal BJP chief}}</ref> On January 28, 2020, he raised another controversy when he questioned why nobody was dying at the [[Shaheen Bagh protests]]\nagainst the [[Citizenship Amendment Act]] when several people had lost their lives waiting to withdraw money from banks during the [[2016 Indian banknote demonetisation|demonetisation]] initiative over three years ago. \"What surprises me is that people were dying after standing in line for two to three hours. But now women and children are sitting in temperatures as low as 4-5 degrees Celsius but nobody is dying! What nectar did they have? I am astonished! What is their incentive (for staying alive)?\" he said at an event organised by the Kolkata Press Club.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news18.com/amp/news/politics/why-no-shaheen-bagh-protester-falling-ill-wonders-dilip-ghosh-2477245.html |title = Why Has No Protester at Shaheen Bagh Fallen Ill or Died Until Now, Asks BJP MP Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/citizenship-amendment-act-bjps-dilip-ghosh-says-many-died-in-notes-ban-queues-why-not-shaheen-bagh-2171141?amp=1&akamai-rum=off | title=\"If 100 Died in Notes Ban Queues, Why Not Shaheen Bagh?\": Shocker by BJP's Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/why-no-shaheen-bagh-protester-falling-ill-wonders-bengal-bjp-chief-dilip-ghosh/1838028/?utm_campaign | title=Why no Shaheen Bagh protester falling ill, wonders Bengal BJP chief Dilip Ghosh| date=28 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/video/why-shaheen-bagh-protester-falling-despite-chilly-winter-dilip-ghosh-1641208-2020-01-29 |title = Why no Shaheen Bagh protester falling ill despite chilly winter: Dilip Ghosh}}</ref> On January 30, he courted yet another controversy with his remark stating that, \"Unless you visit jail, you cannot be a political leader\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.news18.com/news/politics/unless-you-visit-jail-you-cannot-be-a-leader-bengal-bjp-chief-dilip-ghosh-tells-partymen-2479747.html | title=Unless You Visit Jail, You Cannot be a Leader: Bengal BJP Chief Dilip Ghosh Tells Partymen}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/dilip-ghosh-to-bjp-workers-cannot-be-a-leader-unless-you-go-to-jail-2172160 |title = \"Can't be a Leader Unless You Go to Jail\": Dilip Ghosh to BJP Workers}}</ref> His comments drew widespread criticism from opposition parties when a lone woman carrying anti [[Citizenship Amendment Act|CAA]] poster was heckled by his partyman. Later while speaking to newsmen, Ghosh justified the heckling of the woman saying \"Our men did the right thing. She should thank her stars that she was only heckled and nothing else was done to her\".<ref>{{cite news |title=should-thank-her-stars-nothing-else-done-dilip-ghosh-to-anti-caa-protester-heckled-by-bjp-cadres- |url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/should-thank-her-stars-nothing-else-done-dilip-ghosh-to-anti-caa-protester-heckled-by-bjp-cadres-2480201.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.sangbadpratidin.in/kolkata/state-bjp-president-dilip-ghosh-attacks-a-lady-in-patuli/ | title=State BJP president Dilip Ghosh attacks a lady in Patuli| date=30 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://eisamay.indiatimes.com/west-bengal-news/kolkata-news/controversial-comment-of-west-bengal-bjp-president-dilip-ghosh-about-a-lady-who-protested-against-caa-npr-during-bjps-pro-caa-abhinandan-rally/amp_articleshow/73775423.cms |title = Dilip Ghosh: BJP-\u09b0 \u09ae\u09bf\u099b\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7 \u098f\u0995\u09b2\u09be \u09a4\u09b0\u09c1\u09a3\u09c0\u09b0 CAA-\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09bf\u09ac\u09be\u09a6, '\u0993 \u0995\u09bf \u09b6\u09b9\u09bf\u09a6 \u09b9\u09a4\u09c7 \u099a\u09be\u09af\u09bc?' \u09ab\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ac\u09cb\u09ae\u09be \u09a6\u09bf\u09b2\u09c0\u09aa\u09c7\u09b0 - controversial comment of west bengal BJP president dilip ghosh about a lady who protested against caa-NPR during BJP's pro-caa abhinandan rally &#124; Eisamay}}</ref> On February 16, he raked up yet another controversy with his remark on anti [[Citizenship Amendment Act|CAA]] protesters. He said, \"some uneducated, unaware, poor people have been lured with money and are being fed [[Biryani]] with foreign funds to continue with the protests.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/biryani-foreign-funds-driving-the-uneducated-to-caa-rallies-bengal-bjp-president-dilip-ghosh/amp_articleshow/74155796.cms\n|title = Biryani, foreign funds driving the uneducated to CAA rallies: Bengal BJP president Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/protesters-at-delhis-shaheen-bagh-kolkatas-park-circus-uneducated-and-poor-doing-it-for-money-says-bengal-bjp-chief-dilip-ghosh-8045921.html\n|title = Protesters at Delhi's Shaheen Bagh, Kolkata's Park Circus 'uneducated' and 'poor', doing it for money, says Bengal BJP chief Dilip Ghosh}}</ref> On March 11, he claimed that, \"Corona attacks only by staying away from nature, we who live with nature do not have this disease,\" he added, \"To avoid corona, people should dry their clothes in sunlight for 2 hours, which kills the [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|Coronavirus]].\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=\nhttps://zeenews.india.com/india/bjp-mp-dilip-ghosh-suggests-people-living-with-nature-do-not-get-coronavirus-2268912.html|title = Dilip Ghosh suggests people living close to nature do not Coronavirus}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url= https://www.deccanherald.com/amp/national/east-and-northeast/we-are-not-scared-have-gods-blessings-bjps-dilip-ghosh-downplays-coronavirus-threat-812604.html|title = We are not scared, have god's blessings: BJP's Dilip Ghosh downplays coronavirus threat}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=\nhttps://www.thequint.com/news/india/have-gods-blessings-bjp-dilip-ghosh-downplays-coronavirus-threat|title =  Have God\u2019s Blessing\u2019: BJP\u2019s Dilip Ghosh Downplays COVID-19 Threat}}</ref>On March 16, he again claimed that, there is no harm in drinking [[cow urine]] and he has no qualms in admitting he consumes it. He said that, \"For ages, people in our country have consumed urine, all of them have been fit and fine. I have no qualm in accepting that I consume [[Cow Urine]] and will again do so\".The claim that consumption of cow urine can cure coronavirus drew sharp criticism from the ruling [[Trinamool Congress]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/india/story/i-consume-cow-urine-people-have-done-so-for-ages-bjp-west-bengal-chief-dilip-ghosh-1656683-2020-03-18#referrer=https://www.google.com|title= I consume cow urine, people have done so for ages: BJP West Bengal chief Dilip Ghosh}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/east-and-northeast/bengal-bjp-chief-dilip-ghosh-says-no-harm-in-drinking-cow-urine-party-mp-says-time-to-shun-unscientific-beliefs-814873.html| title= Bengal BJP chief Dilip Ghosh says no harm in drinking cow urine; party MP says time to shun 'unscientific beliefs\"\n}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.bjpbengal.org BJP Bengal &#124; Bhartiya Janta Party]\n*[https://www.oheyo.com/bjp-west-bengal BJP Bengal | Video Question and Answer] on [https://www.oheyo.com/ Oheyo]\n\n{{17th Lok Sabha members from all states}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ghosh, Dilip}}\n[[Category:Bengali people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Kolkata]]\n[[Category:Bharatiya Janata Party politicians from West Bengal]]\n[[Category:Bengali Hindus]]\n[[Category:Members of the West Bengal Legislative Assembly]]\n[[Category:Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh members]]\n[[Category:17th Lok Sabha members]]\n[[Category:State Presidents of Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n", "name_user": "Dirkbb", "label": "safe", "com